Description of each path id¶

The paths are divided into mainly three types.

  • Controlled paths : Every subject followed almost the same path. These data are intended for developing the localization algorithms, including comparison of localization results for different subjects. Please note that the same id_path does not guarantee the same path, because the subjects walked while avoiding customers and employees in the facilities.
  • Fingerprint paths : One subject (id_subject=3) walked very slowly in the area and visited almost every location in the floor.
  • Random paths : Every subject was asked to move freely on the floor. These data are intended for evaluation of the localization algorithms. The scoring datasets are sampled from this type of paths.

Correspondence of id_path and path types are as follows.

id_path path type floor
0 Controlled path FLU02
1 Controlled path FLU02
2 Random path FLU02
3 Controlled path FLU02
4 Controlled path FLU01

Following figures show the overview of the paths.

import os
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from PIL import Image

GIS_BASE_PATH = "../release/gis/"
FLOOR_NAMES =  ["FLU01", "FLU02", "FLD01"]
GT_BASE_PATH = "../release/gt"


def load_bitmap(filename):
    image = Image.open(filename)
    array = np.array(image, dtype=bool)
    return array

def plot_map(map_array, dx=0.01, dy=0.01, limit_to_map=True):
    plt.axis("equal")
    
    # plot map
    xmax = map_array.shape[0] * dx # length of map along x axis
    ymax = map_array.shape[1] * dy # length of map along y axis
    cm = plt.imshow(np.rot90(map_array),
               extent=[0, xmax, 0, ymax],cmap="binary", alpha=0.5)

    if limit_to_map:
        plt.xlim(0, xmax)
        plt.ylim(0, ymax)
    
def plot_path(id_path):
    plt.figure()
    floor_name = data_dict[id_path]["df"]["floor"].values[0]
    plot_map(map_dict[floor_name], dx, dy)
    cm = plt.scatter(data_dict[id_path]["df"]["x"], data_dict[id_path]["df"]["y"], c=data_dict[id_path]["df"]["%time"], alpha=0.5, s=0.5)
    plt.colorbar(cm, label="Timestamp(s)")
    plt.plot(data_dict[id_path]["df"]["x"].values[0], data_dict[id_path]["df"]["y"].values[0], "rx", label="start")
    plt.plot(data_dict[id_path]["df"]["x"].values[-1], data_dict[id_path]["df"]["y"].values[-1], "kx", label="end")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel("x (m)")
    plt.ylabel("y (m)")
    plt.title(f"id_path : {id_path} | filename : {data_dict[id_path]['file_path']} | floor : {floor_name}")
    plt.show()


data_dict = {}
# Pick up one file per id_path
for filename in os.listdir(GT_BASE_PATH):
    if filename.endswith(".csv"):
        key = filename.split("_")[0]
        if key not in data_dict:
            file_path = os.path.join(GT_BASE_PATH, filename)
            df = pd.read_csv(file_path)            
            data_dict[key] = {'df': df, 'file_path': os.path.basename(file_path)}
    
# 1 pixel of bmp represents 0.01 m
dx = 0.01
dy = 0.01

# read bitmap image of the floor movable areas
map_dict = {}
for floor_name in FLOOR_NAMES:
    map_dict[floor_name] = load_bitmap(GIS_BASE_PATH + floor_name + "_0.01_0.01.bmp")
